Install using this: https://rizaldijs.wordpress.com/2017/10/28/setting-up-glfw-glad-with-clion-on-ubuntu/

install glew: sudo apt install libglew-dev
install cmake 3.20.0 (if not already there): http://p.ip.fi/6QcG
	Alternatively: https://vitux.com/how-to-install-cmake-on-ubuntu/ (Follow terminal approach)
	
In project folder add:1) cmake/FindGLM.cmake
		       2) CmakeLists.txt  

CmakeLists.txt: http://p.ip.fi/ycYR
		(Replace proj_name with project name and 
		keep updating add_executables whenever you add a new cpp/header file to project)


Check if u can open a blank window from main.cpp: http://p.ip.fi/_lUb

For compiling in terminal:
g++ main.cpp -I/usr/include/libdrm -lglfw -lGLEW -lGLU -lGL

Or can use any other IDE like Clion etc.



